alyses, Nazarian reads early modern sonnets as sites of contestation and collaboration and rewrites the relationship between early modern literary forms.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aEuropean poetryyRenaissance, 1450-1600xHistory and criticism. 0aLiterature and statezEuropexHistoryy16th century. 0aLove poetry, EuropeanxHistory and criticism. 0aViolence in literature. 4aLiterary Studies. 4aMedieval & Renaissance Studies. 4aPoetry & Criticism.  alove poetry, Petrarchan lyric, poet's psychology, politics, post-Petrarchan literary history, Renaissance lyric, early modernity.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066587108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2017z9783110548198oZDB-23-DKU40uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150170826840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501708268423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501708268/original  a978-3-11-062526-4  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017b2017  a978-3-11-066587-1  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2017  aZDB-23-DKUb2017